						<!-- firstHeading -->
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Theme music</span></h1>
			<!-- /firstHeading -->
			<!-- bodyContent -->
			<div id="bodyContent">
								<!-- tagline -->
				<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
				<!-- /tagline -->
								<!-- subtitle -->
				<div id="contentSub">  (Redirected from <a href="../../w/index-title=Theme_songs&redirect=no.php.html" title="Theme songs">Theme songs</a>)</div>
				<!-- /subtitle -->
																<!-- jumpto -->
				<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<!-- /jumpto -->
								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p><b>Theme music</b> is a <a href="Musical_composition" title="Musical composition">piece</a> that is often written specifically for a <a href="Radio_programming" title="Radio programming">radio program</a>, <a href="Television_program" title="Television program">television program</a>, <a href="Video_game" title="Video game">video game</a> or <a href="Movie" title="Movie" class="mw-redirect">movie</a>, and usually played during the intro, during <a href="Title_sequence" title="Title sequence">title sequence</a> and/or ending credits. If it is accompanied by <a href="Lyrics" title="Lyrics">lyrics</a>, most often associated with the show, it is a <b>theme song</b>.</p>
<p>The phrase <b>theme song</b> or <b>signature tune</b> may also be used to refer to a song that has become especially associated with a particular performer or dignitary; often used as they make an entrance.</p>
<p>The purpose of a theme song is often similar to that of a <a href="Leitmotif" title="Leitmotif">leitmotif</a>.</p>
